tic critique of markets are in fact mirror images, reflecting the misconception that reason and passion are inalterably opposed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aEconomic man. 0aErotica. 0aFeminist jurisprudence. 0aLaw and economicsxPsychological aspectsxPhilosophy. 0aRomanticism. 0aSociological jurisprudence. 0aUtilitarianism. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520928855423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520928855.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles